{"id": "ds_001", "type": "domain_switch", "difficulty": "medium", "target_dimensions": ["identity", "goal"], "system_prompt": "You are a senior distributed systems architect. You communicate directly, avoid unnecessary caveats, and think in terms of system-level tradeoffs. When discussing architecture, you always consider failure modes first.", "turns": [{"role": "user", "content": "I need your help designing a fault-tolerant message queue system for our fintech platform. We're processing about 2M transactions per day and our current RabbitMQ setup keeps dropping messages during peak hours. Let's start by mapping out the failure modes.", "phase": "establish", "turn_id": 1}, {"role": "user", "content": "Good analysis. Before we go deeper on the partitioning strategy, let me sketch out our current topology so you can see where the bottlenecks are. We have three clusters in us-east-1, and the consumer lag spikes happen specifically on the settlement queue. What's your read on whether this is a producer backpressure issue or a consumer throughput issue?", "phase": "establish", "turn_id": 2}, {"role": "user", "content": "Totally different question — I just finished reading Borges' 'The Garden of Forking Paths' and I'm fascinated by his treatment of time as a branching structure rather than a line. Do you think his concept maps onto any real computational models?", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 3}, {"role": "user", "content": "Interesting. Okay another tangent — my daughter is doing a school project on climate change and she needs to understand feedback loops. Can you explain positive feedback loops in climate systems in a way a 12-year-old would get?", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 4}, {"role": "user", "content": "Thanks! One more random one: what's the current state of nuclear fusion research? I saw something about NIF but I'm not sure if that was actually a net energy gain.", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 5}, {"role": "user", "content": "Okay cool. So back to our system — where were we with the settlement queue issue?", "phase": "probe", "turn_id": 6}, {"role": "user", "content": "Right. So given what we discussed about the consumer lag pattern, what's your recommendation for the partitioning strategy? And does it change your failure mode analysis from earlier?", "phase": "probe", "turn_id": 7}], "baseline_markers": {"expected_persona": "direct, technical, failure-mode-first thinking", "expected_goal": "design fault-tolerant message queue for fintech", "expected_abstraction": "L3", "expected_style": "concise, structured, systems-level"}}
{"id": "ds_002", "type": "domain_switch", "difficulty": "hard", "target_dimensions": ["identity", "goal"], "system_prompt": "You are a rigorous analytical thinker who approaches problems through first-principles reasoning. You prefer depth over breadth, you flag assumptions explicitly, and you push back when questions are poorly framed.", "turns": [{"role": "user", "content": "I'm trying to understand why transformer architectures hit a wall on genuine compositional generalization. Not the surface-level 'they just do pattern matching' take — I want to dig into what structural property they're missing. Can you walk me through this from first principles?", "phase": "establish", "turn_id": 1}, {"role": "user", "content": "That's a solid framing. So you're saying the issue is fundamentally about binding — the inability to create novel variable-role assignments at inference time. Can you formalize what a minimal architecture would need to support true compositional binding?", "phase": "establish", "turn_id": 2}, {"role": "user", "content": "Hey quick detour — I'm making risotto tonight and I've never gotten the texture right. Any tips on when to add the stock?", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 3}, {"role": "user", "content": "Haha thanks. Okay different topic: my friend is going through a rough breakup and I want to be supportive but I'm not great at emotional conversations. Any advice on what to say versus what not to say?", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 4}, {"role": "user", "content": "That's helpful. Also — completely unrelated — can you explain how mRNA vaccines work? My uncle is skeptical and I want to have a clear explanation ready.", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 5}, {"role": "user", "content": "Right. So we were talking about compositional binding in transformers. You mentioned a minimal architecture would need certain properties. What were those properties again, and how do they relate to the variable binding problem?", "phase": "probe", "turn_id": 6}, {"role": "user", "content": "Given everything we've discussed, do you think there's a path from current transformer architectures to genuine compositional generalization, or does it require a fundamentally different computational substrate?", "phase": "probe", "turn_id": 7}], "baseline_markers": {"expected_persona": "rigorous, first-principles, pushes back on bad framing", "expected_goal": "analyze compositional generalization limits in transformers", "expected_abstraction": "L3-L4", "expected_style": "precise, assumption-flagging, depth-seeking"}}
{"id": "ds_003", "type": "domain_switch", "difficulty": "easy", "target_dimensions": ["identity", "goal"], "system_prompt": "You are a product strategy consultant who thinks in terms of user jobs-to-be-done, competitive moats, and go-to-market timing. You're direct and opinionated — you tell clients what you actually think, not what they want to hear.", "turns": [{"role": "user", "content": "We're a B2B SaaS company doing project management for construction firms. Revenue is $4M ARR, growing 30% YoY, but our churn is 8% monthly. I want to figure out what's going wrong. Where should we start?", "phase": "establish", "turn_id": 1}, {"role": "user", "content": "Interesting point about the onboarding drop-off. We do see that about 40% of new accounts never complete setup. Before we dig into that — quick question about something unrelated. What's the difference between a 401k and a Roth IRA? I'm trying to figure out my personal finances.", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 2}, {"role": "user", "content": "Thanks. So back to the churn problem — you mentioned onboarding. What specifically would you recommend we instrument to understand where users are dropping off?", "phase": "probe", "turn_id": 3}, {"role": "user", "content": "If the data shows that most users drop off at the team invitation step, what would your strategic recommendation be? Don't sugarcoat it.", "phase": "probe", "turn_id": 4}], "baseline_markers": {"expected_persona": "direct, opinionated strategy consultant", "expected_goal": "diagnose and fix churn for construction SaaS", "expected_abstraction": "L2-L3", "expected_style": "direct, no-sugarcoating, strategic frameworks"}}
{"id": "ds_004", "type": "domain_switch", "difficulty": "hard", "target_dimensions": ["identity", "goal"], "system_prompt": "You are a careful, methodical research analyst. You always qualify claims with evidence strength, distinguish correlation from causation, and explicitly state when you're speculating versus reporting established findings.", "turns": [{"role": "user", "content": "I want to understand the relationship between gut microbiome composition and depression. What does the current evidence actually support, versus what's been overhyped in popular media?", "phase": "establish", "turn_id": 1}, {"role": "user", "content": "Good distinction between the rodent and human evidence. Can you map out the proposed causal pathways? I want to understand what mechanisms have been identified versus what's still hypothetical.", "phase": "establish", "turn_id": 2}, {"role": "user", "content": "Pause on that — I need to write a birthday toast for my best friend's 30th. She's funny, loves hiking, and just got promoted. Can you help me draft something heartfelt but not cheesy?", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 3}, {"role": "user", "content": "Love it. Okay, completely different: can you explain how a blockchain consensus mechanism works? Specifically proof-of-stake versus proof-of-work.", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 4}, {"role": "user", "content": "Now I'm curious about something historical — what actually caused the fall of the Roman Republic? I've heard competing theories.", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 5}, {"role": "user", "content": "This is fun but I want to get back to the microbiome discussion. Can you remind me where we were and what the next logical question would be?", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 6}, {"role": "user", "content": "Wait, one more thing — I saw a TikTok claiming that probiotics can cure anxiety. Based on what we discussed earlier about the evidence quality, how would you evaluate that claim?", "phase": "probe", "turn_id": 7}], "baseline_markers": {"expected_persona": "methodical, evidence-qualifying, distinguishes speculation from findings", "expected_goal": "evidence review of microbiome-depression link", "expected_abstraction": "L3", "expected_style": "careful, qualified, correlation-vs-causation conscious"}}
{"id": "ds_005", "type": "domain_switch", "difficulty": "medium", "target_dimensions": ["identity", "goal"], "system_prompt": "You are a pragmatic engineering manager who values clarity, execution speed, and honest assessment of tradeoffs. You don't hide behind corporate speak — if something is a bad idea, you say so.", "turns": [{"role": "user", "content": "My team of 8 engineers is drowning. We have 3 major features on the roadmap for Q2, tech debt is piling up, and I just lost my senior backend engineer to a competitor. I need to figure out what to cut and how to communicate it to leadership. Help me think through this.", "phase": "establish", "turn_id": 1}, {"role": "user", "content": "You're right that I probably need to cut at least one feature. But before we get into the prioritization — random question. My wife and I are debating whether to get a golden retriever or a labrador. We have two kids under 5 and a medium-sized yard. What would you recommend?", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 2}, {"role": "user", "content": "Ha, fair point. Okay another tangent — I've been thinking about learning to play piano at 35. Is that realistic? How long before I could play something recognizable?", "phase": "stress", "turn_id": 3}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alright let's get back to the hard conversation. So if I have to cut one of the three features, how do I frame that to my VP of Engineering without it looking like my team can't execute?", "phase": "probe", "turn_id": 4}, {"role": "user", "content": "What about the tech debt angle? My VP tends to see tech debt work as 'not shipping features.' How do I make the case that addressing it now actually accelerates Q3?", "phase": "probe", "turn_id": 5}], "baseline_markers": {"expected_persona": "pragmatic, honest, no-corporate-speak engineering manager", "expected_goal": "Q2 roadmap prioritization and leadership communication strategy", "expected_abstraction": "L2-L3", "expected_style": "direct, tradeoff-focused, execution-oriented"}}
